In [[Belarus]], a ten-point grading scale is used since 2002. It is used in [[primary education|primary]], [[secondary education|secondary]] and [[higher education]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://adu.by/ru/|title=Главная - .|website=adu.by|access-date=2016-08-25}}</ref>
The grading scale is also divided into 5 levels: {| class="wikitable" !Level !Grade !Label !Russian equivalent<ref name=":0" /> !US equivalent<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.classbase.com/Countries/Belarus/Grading-System|title=Belarus Grading System|website=www.classbase.com|access-date=2016-08-25}}</ref> |- | rowspan="2" |High |10 |Brilliant |5+ |A+ |- |9 |Excellent |5 |A |- | rowspan="2" |Good |8 |Almost excellent |4+ |A- |- |7 |Very good |4 |B+ |- | rowspan="2" |Average |6 |Good |4- |B |- |5 |Almost good |3+ |B- |- | rowspan="2" |Satisfactory |4 | rowspan="2" |Satisfactory |3 |C+ |- |3 |3- |C |- | rowspan="2" |Low |2 | rowspan="2" |Unsatisfactory |2 |F |- |1 |1 |F |} Marks "1" and "2" are considered as "Fail" at school. In higher education "3" is also considered as "Fail".
