{{Infobox university | name = College of Health Sciences | native_name = كلية العلوم الصحية | image_name = College of Health Sciences logo.png | image_size = 150 | image_alt = | caption = Logo of the College | latin_name = | motto = | established = {{start date and age|1959}} | closed = | type = [[Public university]] | calendar = | chairman = | chancellor = | president = | vice-president = | superintendent = | provost = | vice_chancellor = | rector = | principal = | dean = Aneesa Al Sindi | director = | city = [[Manama]] | state = | province = | country = [[Bahrain]] | coor = {{Coord|26|13|1|N|50|34|25|E|display=title}} | former_names = | free_label = | free = | colors = | website = [http://www.uob.edu.bh/en/index.php/colleges/college-of-health-sciences Official website] | logo = }}
The '''College of Health Sciences''' is a publicly run higher education institution in [[Bahrain]].<ref>[http://www.university-directory.eu/Bahrain/College-of-Health-Sciences--Bahrain.html College of Health Sciences, Bahrain], [http://www.university-directory.eu/ University Directory].</ref>
==History== By 1959, a small School of Nursing was established in Bahrain in order to train nurses locally.<ref>[http://www.chs.edu.bh/History.aspx History] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101228222558/http://www.chs.edu.bh/History.aspx |date=2010-12-28 }}, College of Health Sciences, Bahrain.</ref> The College of Health Sciences itself was established in 1976.<ref name="dean">[http://www.chs.edu.bh/Welcome.aspx#Dean Dean's Welcome Message], College of Health Sciences, Bahrain.</ref> It educates and trains health professionals in Nursing and Allied Health under the auspices of the Ministry of Health in Bahrain. Students from other countries in the [[Persian Gulf|Gulf]] region also study at the College.
==Courses== The College offers BSc degrees programme in [[Nursing]] and five Allied Health subjects: [[Dental Hygiene]], Medical Laboratory Technology, [[Pharmacy]], [[Public Health]], and [[Radiography]].<ref name="dean" />
==Campus== The College's campus is in the neighborhood of [[Salmaniya]], in [[Manama]], the capital of Bahrain. It is located within the [[Salmaniya Medical Complex]] (SMC), together with the [[Arabian Gulf University]] and the Salmaniya Hospital.<ref name=Location>[http://www.chs.edu.bh/AboutCampus.aspx College Campus and Facilities] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110110072342/http://www.chs.edu.bh/AboutCampus.aspx |date=2011-01-10 }}, College of Health Sciences, Bahrain.</ref> The campus includes an administration and student affairs building, and multiple nursing and laboratory blocks. Additionally, facilities include a three floor building which hosts multiple offices, classrooms, laboratories and the Ahmed al-Farsi library. It also features the 'Al Ma'arif [[Auditorium]]' which provides a venue for special classes, workshops, meetings, [[seminar]]s and conferences.<ref name=Location/> A computer laboratory was installed in 1988.<ref name=Location/>
