The '''South Asian Institute of Management''' (SAIM) is an independent management institute based in [[Nepal]]. The Institute was opened by a group of professionals who wanted to create an institute of learning, [[research]], and consultancy in the region.<ref>[http://saim.edu.np/about_us/who_we_are.php South Asian Institute of Management website] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100202200402/http://saim.edu.np/about_us/who_we_are.php |date=2010-02-02 }}</ref>
While a [[for profit|profit-making]] venture, the Institute's board decided from the beginning to retain a majority proportion of profits toward institution building and the promotion of [[entrepreneurship]], including backing any promising [[business venture]]s from its own graduates.<ref>[http://www.myrepublica.com/portal/index.php?action=news_details&news_id=7608 myrebulica web site]</ref>
